public interface ICommand<T,E extends Exception>
The iCommand interface defines the contract between the boundary and control layers.

More specifically, it defines the possible actions that can be taken from a specific ConsoleDisplay subclass. Implementations of this class should pass in all necessary parameters through the class constructor and should avoid, as far as possible, requesting input or displaying output within the iCommand class itself.

The iCommand class primarily calls the relevant methods of the necessary control classes required to complete the action for which it is designed. This coordination of methods should be encapsulated within execute(). In this way, the boundary layer only needs to instantiate a new iCommand class and call execute() to perform the desired action.
